OL,6,FAt one point she had a picture
OL,7,Fpostcard life in Musselburgh, on the
OL,8,Feast coast of Scotland, her petrol
OL,9,Fstation business was thriving and her
OL,10,Fchildren grew up by the seaside
OL,11,Fsurrounded by friends.
OL,13,FBut in 2001, Fiona opened a post
OL,14,Foffice and everything changed.
OL,16,F"The Post Office completely changed
OL,17,Fall our lives," her son Daryl
OL,18,Fremembers.
