OL,3,CFamily grieve sub-postmistress who
OL,4,Cdied in mental health spiral
OL,6,FThe effect of remembering those dark
OL,7,Fdays is still clear in Gemma's eyes.
OL,8,FShe was 16, and had tried to help her
OL,9,Fmum in the post office however she
OL,10,Fcould.
OL,12,FShe vividly remembers her mum sitting
OL,13,Fwith piles of paperwork, trying to get
OL,14,Fthrough to the Horizon helpline for
OL,15,Fhours at a time.
OL,17,F"She called the helpline," Gemma says,
OL,18,Ftearful.
OL,20,F"They sent the auditors, and it felt
OL,21,Flike the police."
