OL,4,Cdied in mental health spiral
OL,6,F"However, an apology is of course not
OL,7,Fenough and that is why we are working
OL,8,Fas fast as we can to provide redress
OL,9,Ffor those affected."
OL,11,FDaryl has emailed the Post Office with
OL,12,Fdetails of what happened to his mum,
OL,13,Fbut after waiting a month he still
OL,14,Fhasn't had the courtesy of a reply.
OL,16,F"It's almost adding insult to inquiry
OL,17,Fonce again," Daryl says.
OL,19,F"Somebody needs to be held
OL,20,Faccountable," Gemma tells me.
